# DoneThat Project Structure

## Core Files
- Main entry point: [main.js](mdc:main.js)
- Frontend entry: [src/index.js](mdc:src/index.js)
- Main process state: [src-main/main-state.js](mdc:src-main/main-state.js)

## Key Directories
- `src/`: Frontend code (renderer process)
- `src-main/`: Backend code (main process)
- `resources/`: Static assets and configuration
- `build/`: Compiled assets
- `scripts/`: Build and deployment scripts

## Configuration Files
- Package configuration: [package.json](mdc:package.json)
- Webpack config: [webpack.config.js](mdc:webpack.config.js)
- Firebase config: [firebase-config.js](mdc:firebase-config.js)

## Build Process
1. CSS is built using PostCSS: `npm run build:css`
2. JavaScript is bundled using Webpack: `npm run build:webpack`
3. Full build preparation: `npm run build:prepare`
4. Development: `npm run dev`
5. Production builds: `npm run build`
